  "number": 1113,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1113",
  "title": "starRating widget does not hide when no data",
  "body": "All filtering widgets are hidden when there's no data to be shown.\nThe starRating widget does not. Instead, when no results contain any rating value (ie. everything is `null`), all stars choices are showing, grayed out.\n\nIt is a bit confusing when everything else disappears and only this stays in, but unusable.\n\nThere should probably at least be an option to have the same behavior.\n",
